<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<odoo>
    <!-- Case Study Detail Page Template -->
    <template id="snippet_wf_case_study_detail" name="Warefor Case Study Detail">
        <!-- Hero Section -->
        <section class="wf-cs-hero">
            <img src="/warefor_website/static/src/img/case-containers.jpg" alt="Shipping Containers" class="wf-cs-hero-bg"/>
            <div class="wf-cs-hero-overlay"></div>
            <div class="container">
                <div class="wf-cs-hero-content">
                    <a href="/case-studies" class="wf-cs-back">
                        <i class="fa fa-arrow-left"></i> Back
                    </a>
                    <h1 class="wf-cs-title">Rapid Port Decongestion &amp; Emergency Warehousing</h1>
                    <p class="wf-cs-subtitle">From Crisis Response to Long-Term Partnership</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Image Caption -->
        <div class="wf-cs-caption">
            <p><strong>Illustrative image:</strong> Shipping containers stacked high like a city skyline â€” representing the massive volume of inventory Warefor processed through rapid emergency warehousing deployment.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Content Section -->
        <section class="wf-cs-content">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row justify-content-center">
                    <div class="col-lg-8">
                        <!-- The Challenge -->
                        <div class="wf-cs-section">
                            <h2 class="wf-cs-section-title">The Challenge</h2>
                            <p>During the height of the pandemic, a major national big-box retailer faced severe congestion at U.S. ports. Large volumes of inbound containers were accumulating in costly storage yards, delaying inventory visibility and restricting product flow across their distribution network.</p>
                            <p>The retailer urgently needed to:</p>
                            <ul class="wf-cs-list">
                                <li>Rapidly unload and process containers</li>
                                <li>Receive the merchandise into their systems for visibility &amp; inventory control</li>
                                <li>Restore throughput across their supply chain under extreme time pressure</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <!-- The Solution -->
                        <div class="wf-cs-section">
                            <h2 class="wf-cs-section-title">The Solution</h2>
                            <p>Warefor was engaged to deliver an immediate, large-scale warehousing solution with minimal lead time.</p>
                            <p><strong>Within two weeks, Warefor:</strong></p>
                            <ul class="wf-cs-list">
                                <li>Identified and secured a 375,000 sq. ft. warehouse on a short-term lease</li>
                                <li>Fully cleaned, prepared, and operationalized the facility</li>
                                <li>Began receiving inbound freight the day after the lease was executed</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>As inbound volumes continued to surge, Warefor expanded operations to manage two facilities simultaneously, totaling over 500,000 sq. ft. of active warehouse space operating at near-full capacity.</p>
                            <p><strong>To ensure speed, accuracy, and transparency, Warefor implemented:</strong></p>
                            <ul class="wf-cs-list">
                                <li>Real-time transaction processing</li>
                                <li>Photo-based operational reporting for real-time quality control</li>
                                <li>Proactive communication to ensure uninterrupted flow of containers</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Statistics Grid -->
                        <div class="wf-cs-stats">
                            <div class="wf-cs-stat">
                                <span class="wf-cs-stat-value">4,300+</span>
                                <span class="wf-cs-stat-label">Inbound containers processed</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="wf-cs-stat">
                                <span class="wf-cs-stat-value">3,900+</span>
                                <span class="wf-cs-stat-label">Outbound truckloads dispatched</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="wf-cs-stat">
                                <span class="wf-cs-stat-value">9.25M</span>
                                <span class="wf-cs-stat-label">Cubic feet of merchandise handled</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="wf-cs-stat">
                                <span class="wf-cs-stat-value">0</span>
                                <span class="wf-cs-stat-label">Inventory discrepancies at closeout</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- The Results -->
                        <div class="wf-cs-section">
                            <p>A short-term engagement evolved into a 2.5-year operational partnership.</p>
                            <p>Warefor's execution drew recognition from senior leadership and operations teams, including multiple on-site visits to review best-practice warehouse processes. The operating model developed during this engagement was later referenced as a benchmark for other third-party logistics providers supporting similar initiatives.</p>
                            <p>When the retailer completed additional long-term storage capacity near the port, Warefor:</p>
                            <ul class="wf-cs-list">
                                <li>Successfully wound down operations</li>
                                <li>Emptied both facilities on schedule</li>
                                <li>Delivered zero inventory discrepancies</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Why It Matters Callout -->
                        <div class="wf-cs-callout">
                            <h3 class="wf-cs-callout-title">Why It Matters</h3>
                            <p>This case highlights Warefor's ability to:</p>
                            <ul class="wf-cs-callout-list">
                                <li>Rapidly deploy large-scale capacity in crisis environments</li>
                                <li>Operate with precision, transparency, and control at high volume</li>
                                <li>Act as a trusted extension of complex retail supply chains</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="wf-cs-callout-cta"><strong>When speed, scale, and execution matter most, Warefor delivers.</strong></p>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Final Image -->
                        <div class="wf-cs-final-image">
                            <img src="/warefor_website/static/src/img/warehouse-interior.jpg" alt="Warehouse Interior" class="wf-cs-image"/>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </template>
</odoo>
